INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'de6fc32d-3eef-4a26-b2b9-dd3b32b2b05d',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Phoenix Error Handling — Global Handlers and Consistent Error Responses$escape$,
  $escape$Phoenix centralizes error handling through `Plug.ErrorHandler` and the `FallbackController` pattern. Rather than scattering error logic across controllers, define a fallback module and plug it in with `action_fallback MyAppWeb.FallbackController`. This controller handles `{:error, reason}` tuples returned from controller actions, keeping your happy path clean.

For consistent JSON error responses, implement `call/2` clauses pattern-matching on common error types: `Ecto.Changeset` for validation failures, `:not_found` for missing resources, and `:unauthorized` for auth failures. Each clause renders a structured response with a consistent shape — `%{errors: ..., status: ...}`.

For truly global errors (crashes, unhandled exceptions), override `render/2` in your `ErrorView` (or `ErrorHTML`/`ErrorJSON` in Phoenix 1.7+). The `errors.json` template catches unhandled cases and returns a sanitized message. Pair this with `Plug.ErrorHandler` in your `Endpoint` to intercept 404s and 500s before they hit the default behavior. This two-layer approach — FallbackController for domain errors, ErrorJSON for infrastructure errors — gives you full coverage without duplication.$escape$,
  $escape$defmodule MyAppWeb.FallbackController do
  use MyAppWeb, :controller

  def call(conn, {:error, %Ecto.Changeset{} = changeset}) do
    conn
    |> put_status(:unprocessable_entity)
    |> put_view(json: MyAppWeb.ChangesetJSON)
    |> render(:error, changeset: changeset)
  end

  def call(conn, {:error, :not_found}) do
    conn
    |> put_status(:not_found)
    |> json(%{errors: %{detail: "Resource not found"}})
  end

  def call(conn, {:error, :unauthorized}) do
    conn
    |> put_status(:unauthorized)
    |> json(%{errors: %{detail: "Unauthorized"}})
  end
end$escape$,
  $escape$elixir$escape$,
