INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '7cccec6e-8afa-4757-8bbd-66233b314930',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Phoenix's Generator CLI — Scaffold Smarter with mix phx.gen$escape$,
  $escape$Phoenix's `mix phx.gen.*` commands do far more than stub files — they wire the full vertical slice. `mix phx.gen.live Catalog Product products name:string price:decimal` generates an Ecto schema, migration, context with CRUD functions, a LiveView module, and the router mount in one shot. The `--no-context` and `--no-schema` flags let you attach to an existing context or schema without clobbering it. For JSON APIs, `mix phx.gen.json` skips LiveView and produces controller + Ecto artifacts only. Auth gets its own generator: `mix phx.gen.auth Accounts User users` scaffolds token-based session auth complete with hashed passwords, confirmation emails, and LiveView login flows — nothing you'd want to hand-roll. Hot reload in Phoenix dev mode is handled by `phoenix_live_reload`; file patterns are configured in `config/dev.exs` under the `:live_reload` key. Adding a custom watcher (e.g., a Tailwind CLI process) is a single entry in the `watchers` list — Phoenix spawns and supervises it automatically alongside the server.$escape$,
  $escape$# Generate a full LiveView CRUD feature
mix phx.gen.live Catalog Product products \
  name:string price:decimal stock:integer

# Generate JSON API resources (no LiveView)
mix phx.gen.json Accounts User users email:string:unique

# Scaffold token-based auth (hashing, sessions, confirmation)
mix phx.gen.auth Accounts User users

# config/dev.exs — add a Tailwind watcher
config :my_app, MyAppWeb.Endpoint,
  watchers: [
    tailwind: {Tailwind, :install_and_run, [:default, ~w(--watch)]}
  ]$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
